#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.16"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.16:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.16:0.2"
msgid "2. Nālandavagga"
msgstr "2. At Nālandā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.16:0.3"
msgid "16. Uttiyasutta"
msgstr "16. With Uttiya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.16:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn47.16:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā uttiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno "
"kho āyasmā uttiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Uttiya went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn47.16:1.3"
msgid ""
"“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato "
"dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’"
"ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”"

msgctxt "sn47.16:1.4"
msgid "“Tasmātiha tvaṃ, uttiya, ādimeva visodhehi kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, Uttiya, you should purify the starting point of skillful "
"qualities."

msgctxt "sn47.16:1.5"
msgid "Ko cādi kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ?"
msgstr "What is the starting point of skillful qualities?"

msgctxt "sn47.16:1.6"
msgid "Sīlañca suvisuddhaṃ, diṭṭhi ca ujukā."
msgstr "Well purified ethics and correct view."

msgctxt "sn47.16:1.7"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho te, uttiya, sīlañca suvisuddhaṃ bhavissati, diṭṭhi ca ujukā, "
"tato tvaṃ, uttiya, sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya cattāro satipaṭṭhāne "
"bhāveyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"When your ethics are well purified and your view is correct, you should "
"develop the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, depending on and grounded "
"on ethics."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.16:2.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn47.16:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha tvaṃ, uttiya, kāye kāyānupassī viharāhi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Meditate observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of "
"desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.16:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "Meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.16:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.16:2.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāhi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn47.16:2.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, uttiya, sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya ime cattāro "
"satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāvessasi, tato tvaṃ, uttiya, gamissasi maccudheyyassa "
"pāran”ti."
msgstr ""
"When you develop these four kinds of mindfulness meditation, depending on "
"and grounded on ethics, you’ll pass beyond Death’s domain.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.16:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā uttiyo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"And then Venerable Uttiya approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He "
"got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping "
"him on his right, before leaving."

msgctxt "sn47.16:3.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā uttiyo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto "
"nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, "
"tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then Uttiya, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon "
"realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived "
"having achieved with his own insight the goal for which people from good "
"families rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "sn47.16:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "sn47.16:3.4"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā uttiyo arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Uttiya became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.16:3.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
